data.description: Back on the market as buyer could not perform; property is fully available for showings. Comparable renovations in the area are selling in the mid to high 900's and above. Perfect investor project OR an excellent opportunity for the savvy home owner with a good contractor. Home owner definitely has potential for significant equity after renovation. This is a charming, large semi-detached corner property in the highly sought after Brookland community. This loving home features four bedrooms, two full baths, a separate den on the main floor, a garage, and a private driveway for off street parking. The home boasts 1,656 above-ground sq ft of living area, and includes a formal living room, formal dining room, and a den that can be used as an office or recreational space. The basement has a separate entrance and a full bathroom that is awaiting a makeover. This home is only minutes away from the Brookland-CAU Metro Station, Monroe Street Market, Catholic University and several major bus lines and major driving routes. Don't miss this amazing opportunity to bring your experienced contractor and make this your forever home. House sold strictly “as-is”, seller will make no repairs.
